{
  "doc_id": "31042",
  "text": "Although DCs isolated from cancer patients have been shown to exert cytotoxic activity against malignant cells [CITATION_1] , DC-based immunotherapies mediate antineoplastic effects mainly because they engage the host immune system against malignant lesions [CITATION_2] [CITATION_3] . Thus, all forms of DC-based anticancer interventions constitute paradigms of active immunotherapy.",
